passages.text: Underlying Strength in AECO Drives Solid Beat + Raise

After underperforming post PTC headlines, ADSK delivered an impressive Q beating on all KPIs, driven mainly by AECO strength and confirming their M&A strategy to target strategic deals <10Bn and deliver value to shareholders through buybacks. The update FY26 outlook was just as impressive with revenue and billings targets being raised by 1 pt adjusting for cc and the transaction model. ADSK provided its first look at medium-term operating margin target guiding to 41% (45% exclusive of transaction model) for FY29. While targets seems conservative, we think it is a good starting point to provide upside efficiency to S&M expense over time and we expect to get more information on long-term financial targets at their analyst day on Oct 7. We raise our estimates to the high end of guidance,which moves our TP to $393 and implies 34x FY27 EV/FCF.

**Strong 2Q Print Excluding FX/Transaction Model Noise -** 2Q results were robust with calculated billings growth of +36% y/y beating Citi/consensus estimates by 6 pts with the transaction model contribution $129M to Q2 billings. Revenue grew 18%y/y cc and exceeded the high end of guidance by 2 pts with the transaction model contributing $105M to Q2 revenue. Revenue outperformance was driven by AECO,which grew 24% y/y cc and noted as seeing strong demand in data centers,infrastructure, and industrial buildings. While M&E demand wasn't that impressive (only growing 4% y/y), MFG continued to perform well growing 14% y/y cc. By region Americas and EMEA were particularly strong growing 19% y/y cc each while APAC grew 14% y/y cc. Bookings were also strong in the Q with cRPO accelerating 4 by to 20% y/y and RPO growing 25% y/y. Operating margins were 1 pt above consensus with the management noting some benefits from timing of hiring in the Q. EPS was $2.62 and beat the high end of the guide by ~6.5 pts. FCF was $451M and well ahead of Citi/consensus $185M/205M seeing a strong mix of upfront revenue in the Q.

Raised Guidance and FY29 Operating Margin Targets - The undisturbed FY26 revenue and billings guidance were raised by 1 pt with the company remaining confident in the momentum they are seeing in the business despite any

improvements in the macro environment. The FY26 op margin guide was slightly raised to \(37\%\) (previously \(36.5 - 37\%\) ) and the FCF guide was raised by 4 pts (\$88M) at the midpoint. FCF isn't expected to get a benefit from the BBB in FY27 but management expects to see the benefit hit every year after that. ADSK also decided to give their first look at medium- term targets on the earnings call stating that they expect operating margins for FY29 to be \(41\%\) ( \(45\%\) excluding transaction model) with most of the efficiency coming from S&M over the next few year. We see the FY29 op margin as conservative and good starting point to set expectations for long- term margin improvement. We expect to get more financial updates at their analyst day on Oct 7.

Changes to Estimates — We raise our 3Q revenue targets by 2 pts and 4Q revenue targets by 1 pt, mainly raising subscription revenue in both Qs which puts us above the midpoint of guidance. We align our operating margins with FY26 guidance and our EPS targets are at the high end of guidance. FY26 FCF and billings move to the high end of guidance as we become more confident in the momentum of the business. We flow beat/raise in the Q to our long- term estimates. Our updated regression moves our TP to \$393, which implies 34x FY27 EV/FCF.

Founded in 1982, Autodesk is widely known for its ubiquitous flagship design tool, AutoCAD. Autodesk is a leading provider of 2D and 3D computer- assisted design (CAD) software catering to the architecture, engineering, and construction sector as well as the manufacturing industry. Over the past \(10+\) years, the company has heightened its efforts on expanding its portfolio of products to target broader industry segments such as architecture, construction, and manufacturing. The company's industry- leading products are primarily sold through its vast network of approximately 1,700 channel partners / resellers.

We rate ADsK a Buy. We see a compelling 3- 5 year outlook with high confidence in double- digit growth and expanding margins, likely to drive outsized returns. We believe ADsK is differentiated vs. design/vertical peers with a growth profile that is balanced across several dimensions, including macro/industry tailwinds in construction, infrastructure spending, and manufacturing, as well as company- specific growth drivers (pricing/government contracts & bills / non- compliant user base). Finally, we see ADsK well positioned from an ESG perspective, potentially attracting new investor interest over time.

Our 1- year \(\) 393\(target price uses a'discounted EV'exercise to calculate intrinsic value based on our forecasted operating profile of the business 4 - 5 years from now. The calculated EV implies an EV/FCF multiple of\) - 34xFY27E FCFE of \(\) 2.52\(discounted to a year forward at an 10% discount. The framework that informs our valuation is based off a regression analysis of trading multiples and free cash flow margins of companies across the software universe.
Downside risks that could push the stock below our target price:

1) Macro (inflation and supply chain issues) persist longer and are more severe than expected; 2) Transition to annual contract and M&A transactions fail to drive double-digit FCF CAGR into FY26; and 3) The contribution from conversion of non-compliant user base is prolonged and not achieving the expected contribution to growth.

Citi Research stock recommendations include an investment rating and an optional risk rating to highlight high risk stocks. Risk rating takes into account both price volatility and fundamental criteria. Stocks will either have no risk rating or a High risk rating assigned.

Investment Ratings: Citi Research investment ratings are Buy, Neutral and Sell. Our ratings are a function of analyst expectations of expected total return ("ETR") and risk. ETR is the sum of the forecast price appreciation (or depreciation) plus the dividend yield for a stock within the next 12 months. The target price is based on a 12 month time horizon. The Investment rating definitions are: Buy (1) ETR of \(15\%\) or more or \(25\%\) or more for High risk stocks; and Sell (3) for negative ETR. Any covered stock not assigned a Buy or a Sell is a Neutral (2). For stocks rated Neutral (2), if an analyst believes that there are insufficient valuation drivers and/or investment catalysts to derive a positive or negative investment view, they may elect with the approval of Citi Research management not to assign a target price and, thus, not derive an ETR. Citi Research may suspend its rating and target price and assign "Rating Suspended" status for regulatory and/or internal policy reasons. Citi Research may also suspend its rating and target price and assign "Under Review" status for other exceptional circumstances (e.g. lack of information critical to the analyst's thesis, trading suspension) affecting the company and/or trading in the company's securities. In both such situations, the rating and target price will show as "—" and "–" respectively in the rating history price chart. Prior to 11 April 2022 Citi Research assigned "Under Review" status to both situations and prior to 11 Nov 2020 only in exceptional circumstances. As soon as practically possible, the analyst will publish a note re- establishing a rating and investment thesis. Investment ratings are determined by the ranges described above at the time of initiation of coverage, a change in investment and/or risk rating, or a change in target price (subject to limited management discretion). At times, the expected total returns may fall outside of these ranges because of market price movements and/or other short- term volatility or trading patterns. Such interim deviations will be permitted but will become subject to review by Research Management. Your decision to buy or sell a security should be based upon your personal investment objectives and should be made only after evaluating the stock's expected performance and risk.

Catalyst Watch and STV Upside/Downsides calls: Citi Research may also include a Catalyst Watch or STV Upside or Downside call to indicate the analyst expects the share price to rise (fall) in absolute terms over a specified period of 30 or 90 days in reaction to one or more specific near- term catalysts or events impacting the company or the market. A Catalyst Watch will be published when Analyst confidence is high that an impact to share price will occur; it will be a STV when confidence level is moderate. A Catalyst Watch or STV Upside/Downside call will automatically expire at the end of the specified 30/90 day period.
